hh3cEponUni.name: hh3cEponUni
hh3cEponUni.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cEponUni.description: The objects in this MIB module are used to manage and display current configuration of UNI (user network interface) which is based on the ONU(Optical Network Unit).

hh3cEponUniSysManTable.name: hh3cEponUniSysManTable
hh3cEponUniSysManTable.description: This table defines several UNI system parameters.

hh3cEponUniIndex.name: hh3cEponUniIndex
hh3cEponUniIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the FE(fast Ethernet) interface of the ONU.

hh3cEponUniDescr.name: hh3cEponUniDescr
hh3cEponUniDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware and software.

hh3cEponUniAdminStatus.name: hh3cEponUniAdminStatus
hh3cEponUniAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the user network interface. When a managed system initializes, all user network interfaces start with down(2) state. The testing(3)state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, hh3cEponUniAdminStatus is then changed to either the up(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the down(2) state).

hh3cEponUniMdi.name: hh3cEponUniMdi
hh3cEponUniMdi.description: Type of the line connected to UNI interface: mdi-ii(straight-through cable), mdi-x (crossover cable), mdi-auto (auto-sensing).

hh3cEponUniPriority.name: hh3cEponUniPriority
hh3cEponUniPriority.description: The priority of user network interface. If the value is larger, the priority will be higher.

hh3cEponUniAccessVlan.name: hh3cEponUniAccessVlan
hh3cEponUniAccessVlan.description: The vlan ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on user network interface.

hh3cEponUniTrunkPvid.name: hh3cEponUniTrunkPvid
hh3cEponUniTrunkPvid.description: PVID(port vlan ID), the vlan ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on user network interface.

hh3cEponUniVLANTrunkAllowListLow.name: hh3cEponUniVLANTrunkAllowListLow
hh3cEponUniVLANTrunkAllowListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 1 through 8, the second octet specifying vlans 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each allowed vlan of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that vlan is allowed in the set of vlans. the vlan is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hh3cEponUniVLANTrunkAllowListHigh.name: hh3cEponUniVLANTrunkAllowListHigh
hh3cEponUniVLANTrunkAllowListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying vlans 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered vlan, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered vlan. Thus, each allowed vlan of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that vlan is allowed in the set of vlans; the vlan is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hh3cEponUniInboundLineRate.name: hh3cEponUniInboundLineRate
hh3cEponUniInboundLineRate.description: The value of the inbound line-rate. measured with kbps. The upper limit of the line-rate is the value of hh3cEponUniLineRateMax in the entry. It must be multiple of the value of hh3cEponUniLineRateStep. The default value of hh3cEponUniLineRate is the value of hh3cEponUniLineRateMax.

hh3cEponUniOutboundLineRate.name: hh3cEponUniOutboundLineRate
hh3cEponUniOutboundLineRate.description: The value of the outbound line-rate. measured with kbps. The upper limit of the line-rate is the value of hh3cEponUniLineRateMax in the entry. It must be multiple of the value of hh3cEponUniLineRateStep. The default value of hh3cEponUniLineRate is the value of hh3cEponUniLineRateMax.

hh3cEponUniFlowControl.name: hh3cEponUniFlowControl
hh3cEponUniFlowControl.description: Flow control status. true(1) - Flow control status enable. false(2) - Flow control status disable.

hh3cEponUniVlanVPNStatus.name: hh3cEponUniVlanVPNStatus
hh3cEponUniVlanVPNStatus.description: vlan VPN status. true(1) - vlan VPN status enable. false(2) - vlan VPN disable.

hh3cEponUniCountReset.name: hh3cEponUniCountReset
hh3cEponUniCountReset.description: Reset the counter which is about packets of the interface, then the counter will change to zero. There is no sense in reading this object.

hh3cEponUniPortIsolate.name: hh3cEponUniPortIsolate
hh3cEponUniPortIsolate.description: enable - enable UNI port isolate setting. disable - disable UNI port isolate setting.

hh3cEponUniVlanConfiguration.name: hh3cEponUniVlanConfiguration
hh3cEponUniVlanConfiguration.description: The vlan configuration of the related vlan mode. Transparent vlan mode: hh3cEponUniVlanConfiguration is a zero length string. Tag vlan mode: the first four octets were the tag assigned to untagged frames received on UNI, including TPID, VID,CFI and priority. Translation vlan mode: the first four octets were the old tag (including TPID, VID, CFI and priority), which is replaced by the new tag(including TPID, VID, CFI and priority), the second four octets.

hh3cEponUniAutoNegotiation.name: hh3cEponUniAutoNegotiation
hh3cEponUniAutoNegotiation.description: enable - enable auto negotiation. disable - disable auto negotiation.

hh3cEponUniRestartAutoNeg.name: hh3cEponUniRestartAutoNeg
hh3cEponUniRestartAutoNeg.description: Force to restart the auto negotiation process.

hh3cEponUniVitualCableTest.name: hh3cEponUniVitualCableTest
hh3cEponUniVitualCableTest.description: True(1): Virtual cable test enable. False(2): Virtual cable test disable.

hh3cEponUniVCTCableStatus.name: hh3cEponUniVCTCableStatus
hh3cEponUniVCTCableStatus.description: Get the cable status. Normal(1),cable is normal. Abnormal(2),cable is abnormal. AbnormalOpen(3),cable is abnormal because of open circuit. AbnormalShort(4),cable is abnormal because of short circuit. Failure(5),cable is abnormal because of testing failure.

hh3cEponUniVCTCableLength.name: hh3cEponUniVCTCableLength
hh3cEponUniVCTCableLength.description: Get the cable length. When hh3cEponUniVCTCableStatus is normal, the node stands for the length from the UNI port to the port opposite. When hh3cEponUniVCTCableStatus is abnormal, it stands for the lengh from the UNI port to the failure place. Unit:meter(m).

hh3cEponUniVCTImpedanceMismatch.name: hh3cEponUniVCTImpedanceMismatch
hh3cEponUniVCTImpedanceMismatch.description: Get the cable impedance. Not-support(1),the UNI port does not support this function. True(2),impedance match. False(3),impedance mismatch.

hh3cEponUniVCTPairSkew.name: hh3cEponUniVCTPairSkew
hh3cEponUniVCTPairSkew.description: Get the symmetry of cable. If the function is not supported, the default value 0 will be returned. Unit:nanosecond(ns).

hh3cEponUniVCTPairSwap.name: hh3cEponUniVCTPairSwap
hh3cEponUniVCTPairSwap.description: NotSupport(1),the UNI port does not support this function. True(2),pair swap. False(3),not pair swap.

hh3cEponUniVCTPolaritySwap.name: hh3cEponUniVCTPolaritySwap
hh3cEponUniVCTPolaritySwap.description: NotSupport(1),the UNI port does not support this function. True(2),polarity swap. False(3),not polarity swap.

hh3cEponUniVCTInsertionLoss.name: hh3cEponUniVCTInsertionLoss
hh3cEponUniVCTInsertionLoss.description: If the function is not supported, the default value 0 will be returned. Unit:decibel(db).

hh3cEponUniVCTReturnLoss.name: hh3cEponUniVCTReturnLoss
hh3cEponUniVCTReturnLoss.description: If the function is not supported, the default value 0 will be returned. Unit:decibel(db).

hh3cEponUniVCTNearendCrosstalk.name: hh3cEponUniVCTNearendCrosstalk
hh3cEponUniVCTNearendCrosstalk.description: If the function is not supported, the default value 0 will be returned. Unit:decibel(db).

hh3cEponUniVlan.name: hh3cEponUniVlan
hh3cEponUniVlan.description: If the function is not supported, the default value 0 will be returned. Unit:decibel(db).

hh3cEponUniCountTable.name: hh3cEponUniCountTable
hh3cEponUniCountTable.description: A list of interface counter about frames entries.

hh3cEponUniCountEntry.name: hh3cEponUniCountEntry
hh3cEponUniCountEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

hh3cEponUniInStatsPkts.name: hh3cEponUniInStatsPkts
hh3cEponUniInStatsPkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames, broadcast frames, and multicast frames) received.

hh3cEponUniInStatsUnicastPkts.name: hh3cEponUniInStatsUnicastPkts
hh3cEponUniInStatsUnicastPkts.description: The total number of good frames received that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast frames.

hh3cEponUniInStatsBroadcastPkts.name: hh3cEponUniInStatsBroadcastPkts
hh3cEponUniInStatsBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of good frames received that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast frames.

hh3cEponUniInStatsMulticastPkts.name: hh3cEponUniInStatsMulticastPkts
hh3cEponUniInStatsMulticastPkts.description: The total number of good frames received that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include frames directed to the broadcast address.

hh3cEponUniInPausePkts.name: hh3cEponUniInPausePkts
hh3cEponUniInPausePkts.description: A count of MAC Control frames received on this interface by the pause(flow control) operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hh3cEponUniInTotalErrors.name: hh3cEponUniInTotalErrors
hh3cEponUniInTotalErrors.description: Total count of the error frames received on this interface.

hh3cEponUniInStatsCRCAlignErrors.name: hh3cEponUniInStatsCRCAlignErrors
hh3cEponUniInStatsCRCAlignErrors.description: The total number of frames received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

hh3cEponUniInStatsUndersizePkts.name: hh3cEponUniInStatsUndersizePkts
hh3cEponUniInStatsUndersizePkts.description: The total number of frames received that are less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

hh3cEponUniInStatsOversizePkts.name: hh3cEponUniInStatsOversizePkts
hh3cEponUniInStatsOversizePkts.description: The total number of frames received that are longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

hh3cEponUniInErrorbyOther.name: hh3cEponUniInErrorbyOther
hh3cEponUniInErrorbyOther.description: The total number of error frames received on this interface.

hh3cEponUniOutStatsPkts.name: hh3cEponUniOutStatsPkts
hh3cEponUniOutStatsPkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames, broadcast frames, and multicast frames) sent.

hh3cEponUniOutStatsUnicastPkts.name: hh3cEponUniOutStatsUnicastPkts
hh3cEponUniOutStatsUnicastPkts.description: The total number of good frames sent that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast frames.

hh3cEponUniOutStatsBroadcastPkts.name: hh3cEponUniOutStatsBroadcastPkts
hh3cEponUniOutStatsBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of good frames sent that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast frames.

hh3cEponUniOutStatsMulticastPkts.name: hh3cEponUniOutStatsMulticastPkts
hh3cEponUniOutStatsMulticastPkts.description: The total number of good frames sent that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include frames directed to the broadcast address.

hh3cEponUniOutStatsPausePkts.name: hh3cEponUniOutStatsPausePkts
hh3cEponUniOutStatsPausePkts.description: The total number of MAC control frames sent on this interface by the pause operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hh3cEponUniOutTotalErrors.name: hh3cEponUniOutTotalErrors
hh3cEponUniOutTotalErrors.description: The total number of error frames sent on this interface.

hh3cEponUniOutStatsCollisions.name: hh3cEponUniOutStatsCollisions
hh3cEponUniOutStatsCollisions.description: The best estimate of the total number of collisions on this Ethernet segment. The value returned will depend on the location of the RMON probe. Section 8.2.1.3 (10BASE-5) and section 10.3.1.3 (10BASE-2) of IEEE standard 802.3 states that a station must detect a collision, in the receive mode, if three or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. A repeater port must detect a collision when two or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. Thus a probe placed on a repeater port could record more collisions than a probe connected to a station on the same segment could. Probe location plays a much smaller role when considering 10BASE-T. 14.2.1.4 (10BASE-T) of IEEE standard 802.3 defines a collision as the simultaneous presence of signals on the DO and RD circuits (transmitting and receiving at the same time). A 10BASE-T station can only detect collisions when it is transmitting. Thus probes placed on a station and a repeater, should report the same number of collisions. Note also that an RMON probe inside a repeater should ideally report collisions between the repeater and one or more other hosts (transmit collisions as defined by IEEE 802.3k) plus receiver collisions observed on any coax segments to which the repeater is connected.

hh3cEponUniOutDelayExceededDiscards.name: hh3cEponUniOutDelayExceededDiscards
hh3cEponUniOutDelayExceededDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to excessive transit delay through the bridge. It is incremented by both transparent and source route bridges.

hh3cEponUniOutErrorbyOther.name: hh3cEponUniOutErrorbyOther
hh3cEponUniOutErrorbyOther.description: The total number of other error frames sent on this interface. Other error frames means the error frames out of collision frames and excessive delayed frames.

hh3cEponUniOutDroppedFrames.name: hh3cEponUniOutDroppedFrames
hh3cEponUniOutDroppedFrames.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer failure.

hh3cEponUniIgmpInfoTable.name: hh3cEponUniIgmpInfoTable
hh3cEponUniIgmpInfoTable.description: This table stores igmp information of UNI interface.

hh3cEponUniMacIndex.name: hh3cEponUniMacIndex
hh3cEponUniMacIndex.description: The index uniquely identifies the igmp information in current UNI interface.

hh3cEponUniIgmpMacAddress.name: hh3cEponUniIgmpMacAddress
hh3cEponUniIgmpMacAddress.description: A 6-octet read-only value carrying the individual MAC address indicates which igmp group the UNI interface belonging to.

hh3cEponUniIgmpVlanId.name: hh3cEponUniIgmpVlanId
hh3cEponUniIgmpVlanId.description: An integer range from 1 to 4094 indicates the vlan which the igmp Mac address has joined in.

hh3cEponUniLineRateMax.name: hh3cEponUniLineRateMax
hh3cEponUniLineRateMax.description: The maximum value of the line-rate(kbps) that user network interface can be set.

hh3cEponUniNumberOnOnu.name: hh3cEponUniNumberOnOnu
hh3cEponUniNumberOnOnu.description: The user network interface number on ONU.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyStatus.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyStatus
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyStatus.description: enable - enable UNI upstream port policing. disable - disable UNI upstream port policing.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyCir.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyCir
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyCir.description: The committed information rate, ranging from 1 to 102400, measured in kbps.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyBucketDepth.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyBucketDepth
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyBucketDepth.description: The depth of the token bucket to tolerant the certain burst(CBS), ranging from 0 to 65535, measured in bytes.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyExtraBurst.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyExtraBurst
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyExtraBurst.description: The extra token to permit the forwarding engine to finish the packet being sent when the bucket depth is exhausted, ranging from 0 to 65535, measured in bytes.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundCir.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundCir
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundCir.description: The inbound committed information rate, measured in kbps.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundBucketDepth.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundBucketDepth
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundBucketDepth.description: The inbound depth of the token bucket to tolerant the certain burst(CBS), ranging from 0 to 65535, measured in bytes.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundExtraBurst.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundExtraBurst
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyInboundExtraBurst.description: The inbound extra token to permit the forwarding engine to finish the packet being sent when the bucket depth is exhausted, ranging from 0 to 65535, measured in bytes.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyOutboundCir.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyOutboundCir
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyOutboundCir.description: The outbound committed information rate, stepped by 64, measured in kbps.

hh3cEponUniPortPolicyOutboundPir.name: hh3cEponUniPortPolicyOutboundPir
hh3cEponUniPortPolicyOutboundPir.description: The outbound peak information rate, stepped by 64, measured in kbps.

hh3cEponUniMulticastGroupNumber.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastGroupNumber
hh3cEponUniMulticastGroupNumber.description: The allowed multicast group number that can be handled at the same time by UNI.

hh3cEponUniMulticastVlanList.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastVlanList
hh3cEponUniMulticastVlanList.description: The multicast vlan list. The first two octets of the string represent the first VLAN ID; the second two octets of the string represent the second VLAN ID, and so on. It is a zero length string by default.

hh3cEponUniMulticastStripStatus.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastStripStatus
hh3cEponUniMulticastStripStatus.description: true - strip the vlan tag of multicast packet. false - does not strip the vlan tag of multicast packet.

hh3cEponUniMulticastFastleave.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastFastleave
hh3cEponUniMulticastFastleave.description: true(1) - fast leave of IGMP enable on ONU. false(2) - fast leave of IGMP disable on ONU.

hh3cEponUniLocalTechAbility.name: hh3cEponUniLocalTechAbility
hh3cEponUniLocalTechAbility.description: The local port capabilities of the UNI. Each two octets stand for a capability of UNI: the first two octets represent one capability and the second two octets represent another capability, and so on. The capabilities list: 1 - undefined, 2 - initializing, true ability not yet known, 14 - 10BASE-T, 142 - full duplex 10BASE-T, 23 - 100BASE-T4, 25 - 100BASE-TX, 252 - full duplex 100BASE-TX, 312 - PAUSE operation for full duplex links, 313 - asymmetric PAUSE operation for full duplex links, 314 - symmetric PAUSE operation for full duplex links, 32 - 100BASE-T2, 322 - full duplex 100BASE-T2, 36 - 1000BASE-X, 362 - full duplex 1000BASE-X, 40 - 1000BASE-T UTP PHY, 402 - full duplex 1000BASE-T UTP PHY, 37 - remote fault bit 1(RF1), 372 - remote fault bit 2(RF2), 8029 - 802.9ISLAN-16T.

hh3cEponUniAdvertisedTechAbility.name: hh3cEponUniAdvertisedTechAbility
hh3cEponUniAdvertisedTechAbility.description: The advertised port capabilities of the UNI. The capabilities list references the description of hh3cEponUniLocalTechAbility.

hh3cEponUniMulticastControlEntry.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastControlEntry
hh3cEponUniMulticastControlEntry.description: The entry of the table hh3cEponUniMulticastControlTable.

hh3cEponUniMulticastAddressList.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastAddressList
hh3cEponUniMulticastAddressList.description: The multicast address, each four octets represents a multicast address, the address section ranging from the first four octets to the second four octets, and the like.

hh3cEponUniMulticastAccessRule.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastAccessRule
hh3cEponUniMulticastAccessRule.description: deny - deny the multicast packet. permit - permit the multicast packet. preview - permit the multicast packet with conditions.

hh3cEponUniMulticastChannelLimit.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastChannelLimit
hh3cEponUniMulticastChannelLimit.description: The limitation of multicast preview channel number.

hh3cEponUniMulticastPreTimeSlice.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastPreTimeSlice
hh3cEponUniMulticastPreTimeSlice.description: The time slice of multicast preview.

hh3cEponUniMulticastPreTimes.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastPreTimes
hh3cEponUniMulticastPreTimes.description: The number of multicast preview times.

hh3cEponUniMulticastPreInterval.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastPreInterval
hh3cEponUniMulticastPreInterval.description: The interval between two consecutive previews, measured in minute.

hh3cEponUniMulticastRowStatus.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastRowStatus
hh3cEponUniMulticastRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The active, createAndGo and the destory statuses are supported.

hh3cEponUniMulticastSourceIpList.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastSourceIpList
hh3cEponUniMulticastSourceIpList.description: This list contains many source ip addresses. Each ip address is contained in four octets.

hh3cEponUniMulticastResetInterval.name: hh3cEponUniMulticastResetInterval
hh3cEponUniMulticastResetInterval.description: The interval is measured in minute. From the last preview limitation is reached, a customer can preview again after this interval is expired.

hh3cEponUniQosIndexNextEntry.name: hh3cEponUniQosIndexNextEntry
hh3cEponUniQosIndexNextEntry.description: The entry of the table hh3cEponUniQosIndexNextTable.

hh3cEponUniQosConfIndexNext.name: hh3cEponUniQosConfIndexNext
hh3cEponUniQosConfIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for hh3cEponUniQosConfIndex when creating rows in the hh3cEponUniQosConfTable.

hh3cEponUniQosConfEntry.name: hh3cEponUniQosConfEntry
hh3cEponUniQosConfEntry.description: The entry of the table hh3cEponUniQosConfTable.

hh3cEponUniQosConfRuleIndexNext.name: hh3cEponUniQosConfRuleIndexNext
hh3cEponUniQosConfRuleIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for hh3cEponUniQosRuleIndex when creating rows in the hh3cEponUniQosRuleTable.

hh3cEponUniQosConfMappedQueue.name: hh3cEponUniQosConfMappedQueue
hh3cEponUniQosConfMappedQueue.description: The queue that the ethernet frames will be mapped.

hh3cEponUniQosConfMarkedPriority.name: hh3cEponUniQosConfMarkedPriority
hh3cEponUniQosConfMarkedPriority.description: Priority of the ethernet frames to be marked, which compliant with the 802.1D user priority standard.

hh3cEponUniQosConfRowStatus.name: hh3cEponUniQosConfRowStatus
hh3cEponUniQosConfRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The active, createAndGo and the destory statuses are supported.

hh3cEponUniQosRuleTable.name: hh3cEponUniQosRuleTable
hh3cEponUniQosRuleTable.description: Qos sub rule of the UNI.

hh3cEponUniQosRuleEntry.name: hh3cEponUniQosRuleEntry
hh3cEponUniQosRuleEntry.description: The entry of the table hh3cEponUniQosRuleTable.

hh3cEponUniQosRuleSelector.name: hh3cEponUniQosRuleSelector
hh3cEponUniQosRuleSelector.description: The ethernet frame selector. dstmac - based on destination MAC address. srcmac - based on source MAC address. ethernetpriority - based on ethernet priority. vlanid - based on VLAN ID. ethernettype - based on ethernet type. dstip - based on destination IP address. srcip - based on source IP address. ipprototype - based on IP type(ipv4 or ipv6). ipv4tosdscp - based on IP TOS/DSCP. ipv6 - based IP precedence. srcport - based on layer 4 source port. dstport - based on layer 4 destination port.

hh3cEponUniQosRuleValue.name: hh3cEponUniQosRuleValue
hh3cEponUniQosRuleValue.description: The rule value based on the hh3cEponUniQosRuleSelector.

hh3cEponUniQosRuleOperator.name: hh3cEponUniQosRuleOperator
hh3cEponUniQosRuleOperator.description: nervermatch - value never match. equal - field equal to the value. notequal - field not equal to the value. lessthanequal - field less than or equal to the value. greaterthanequal - field greater than or equal to the value. fieldexist - value is ignored if field exists. fieldnotexist - value is ignored if field does not exist. alwaysmatch - value always match.

hh3cEponUniQosRuleRowStatus.name: hh3cEponUniQosRuleRowStatus
hh3cEponUniQosRuleRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. Only active, createAndGo and the destory are supported.

hh3cEponUniMirrorGroupTable.name: hh3cEponUniMirrorGroupTable
hh3cEponUniMirrorGroupTable.description: Qos sub rule of the UNI.

hh3cEponUniMirrorInboundPortList.name: hh3cEponUniMirrorInboundPortList
hh3cEponUniMirrorInboundPortList.description: UNI inbound port list. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered UNI, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered UNI. Thus, each UNI port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is allowed in the set of ports. the port is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.
